The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Good Morning

 Hello It's Thursday, November 18, 2004

 Roads to avoid

 Beadon Street, from JM Avenue crossing, and Nimtala Ghat Street, noon to 8 pm. Chhat puja processions. 

 True spirit

 The True Spirit Puja Felicitation Ceremony will be held at GD Birla Sabhagar, 6.30 pm. Lakkhichhara will perform at the function. 

 Interface

 An interactive session with Sir V.S. Naipaul at Oxford Bookstore, 6.30 pm. Amit Chaudhuri will moderate a discussion on his works. Victor Banerjee will read from Magic Seeds. By invitation only.

 On stage

 Shekor (Roots?), featuring play-readings, poetry-readings, enactments and music recitals, at Caf? Coffee Day, 59, Ballygunge Circular Road, 7 pm. 

 Soiree

 A violin recital by D.K. Datar at Ramakrishna Mission Institute of Culture, 6 pm.

 Chhotii Si Asha, a musical programme based on the Global Movement for Children at Bharatiyam, 10 am. 

 Exhibition

 An exhibition on Indian Institute of Cerebral Palsy, on its premises, 10.30 am to 4 pm.




